programme.title: Fireman Sam
programme.desc: The Wildmen of Pontypandy (Moose and Tom) are taking the Pontypandy Pioneers (Mandy, Norman, Derek, Sarah and Trevor) up the mountain for a wilderness outing.

programme.title: Pfffirates
programme.desc: (AD) Pat and Stede accuse Lily of taking decisions too lightly, making her doubt herself. A crooked skull she stumbles upon gives her valuable advice for that day's challenge. But she starts depending on it for guidance.

programme.title: Bluey
programme.desc: (AD) Bluey and Bingo are making mud pizzas and delivering them to the grownups, but their pedal car's wheel keeps falling off!

programme.title: Molly And Mack
programme.desc: Suki and Daisy go to Mrs Anderson's farm to check on Willow the Goat. James and Mack have fun with a remote control car, but things get a bit out of hand and Moira's not happy.

programme.title: Brave Bunnies
programme.desc: When Bop and Boo meet Flou Lou, a loud little lemur, the Bunnies learn to play a unique new instrument, while showing their new friend how to make his music more melodic.

programme.title: Sally & Possum
programme.desc: It is only a little bit of water dripping from the tap. But what happens when it keeps going drip, drip, drip. Possum and Skip to the rescue!

programme.title: Sarah & Duck
programme.desc: Sarah and Duck are going to take Umbrella to the Big Shop, but Umbrella misses the stop to get off.

programme.title: In The Night Garden
programme.desc: The Pontipines are eating their Pontipine dinner, when Mr Pontipine's moustache flies off! First it gets stuck on the chimney, then the bridge and then the gazebo.

programme.title: Buddi
programme.desc: (AD) On the top of Buddi Mountain, the Buddis find parts of a mysterious colourful machine scattered on the ground. They find they can put the pieces together like a puzzle.

programme.title: Tik Tak
programme.desc: Explore a Claymation apple, magic flowers and watch Book Boy makes a mirror by doing magic.

programme.title: Twirlywoos
programme.desc: The Twirlywoos visit a school hall. The teacher comes in and picks up a hoop and spins it, then another and another. She leaves them lying flat on the floor. The Twirlywoos set all the hoops spinning at the same time.

programme.title: Do, Re & Mi
programme.desc: When the friends lose their way in the forest, they retrace their steps by following the sounds they heard on their way in.

programme.title: Peppa Pig
programme.desc: Peppa and George go behind the scenes to find out how TV is made. Miss Rabbit shows them around the set of Super Potato.

programme.title: Pins And Nettie
programme.desc: The Narrator brought her new kitten with her today. But the hedgehogs aren't so sure and are going to need some help warming up to her.

programme.title: Mister Maker Around The World
programme.desc: Mister Maker, Scrappz and Tocky find out how to make something prehistoric in South America. In Australia, discover if Mister Maker can make a gorgeous glitter badge. And see what's cooking in a Hong Kong street market.

programme.title: Ana Pumpkin
programme.desc: Ana, Buddy and Rick work in the garden while the neighbors have a water fight. When Rick won't let them have one too, Ana comes up with a plan to make it happen.

programme.title: Guess How Much I Love You
programme.desc: Little Nutbrown Hare and Little Field Mouse innocently pick lots of spring flowers from a field and deliver bunches to their friends.

programme.title: hoopla doopla!
programme.desc: Bop's job is to wind the town clock before everyone wakes up. He decides to move the clock forward so his friends wake up earlier and morning tea will be earlier, but everyone in Hoopla relies on the clock being on time.

programme.title: Pip And Posy
programme.desc: (AD) Pip and Posy are decorating pancakes when Posy suggests they create pancake portraits of each other. It's great fun until they have different ideas about the best way to do it.

programme.title: Grace's Amazing Machines
programme.desc: Grace shows off machines that all move in a really cool way! Grace has a drive in a lowrider and makes it bounce, shows off a car that can drive over other cars in a traffic jam, and does some cool donuts in a drift car.

programme.title: Thomas And Friends: Big World! Big Adventures!
programme.desc: Philip learns that sometimes even the smallest engine's actions can make them the bigger engine.

programme.title: Dot.
programme.desc: Inspired by her growing collection of postcards from Nana, Dot decides to send Nana a postcard of her own.

programme.title: The Most Magnificent Thing
programme.desc: A young girl receives a tool kit from her mum and decides to make something for her faithful dog. Through trial and error and wrestling with creative doubts, she persists until she builds the most magnificent thing of all.

programme.title: Cookie Monster's Foodie Truck
programme.desc: Cookie Monster and Gonger are Monster Foodies! They get a call and take an order from their friend who needs help with making baba ghanoush with pita bread, one of their family's favorite foods.

programme.title: Play School: Let's Take a Ride
programme.desc: (AD) What will the Play School Get-Set-Go Mobile be today? Toot-toot, a taxi! Emma and Teo play at the fun park, make a story salad, and visit the craft-made carnival before the long ride home.

programme.title: Andy's Wild Adventures
programme.desc: Andy takes Kip on a Wild Adventure to see Flamingos in Kenya. He dances with a million pink Flamingos and then uses Kip's invention to surf across the mud so he can visit the tiny chicks in their nest.

programme.title: Floogals
programme.desc: While trying to find Boy Hooman's school pet in its tank Fleeker accidentally lets it escape. His frustration mounts as the stick insect 'camouflage' skill mean it eludes him at every turn.

programme.title: School Of Roars
programme.desc: The monsters make 'shoebox caves' and put little models of their families inside. But Wingston feels sad because he doesn't have a mummy in his family.

programme.title: Go Jetters
programme.desc: Lars is very excited! The Go Jetters are going to Iceland, where the World's largest colony of Atlantic puffins gathers every year.

programme.title: Remy And Boo
programme.desc: (AD) After a baby duckling imprints on Boo, he excitedly accepts the role of being mama until the real mother returns to its nest. But looking after a rambunctious baby turns out to be way more work than Remy and Boo imagined!

programme.title: Peppa Pig
programme.desc: George pays a visit to Mr Fox's Shop after his favourite toy, Mr Dinosaur breaks. With all the additional features surely Dino Roar is a good replacement?

programme.title: Pfffirates
programme.desc: (AD) The Korsairs accidentally make a hole in the island with a super powerful cannonballoon, the "Perforator." Then make it worse trying to fix it as the island crumples noticeably. Will they succeed, before it sags completely?

programme.title: Lu and the Bally Bunch
programme.desc: Elodie upsets Lu when she forgets her promise to push her on the swing.

programme.title: Ginger And The Vegesaurs
programme.desc: (AD) When Ginger gets a nasty tummy ache, the Pea-Rexes have to find a special soothing herb which unfortunately is in the middle of Bananaraptor island!

programme.title: Kiya and the Kimoja Heroes
programme.desc: (AD) When Zane pretends that he has seen the sprites that protect the fireflies living around the Baobab tree, Kiya gets an irresistible urge to see them too.

programme.title: Nella the Princess Knight
programme.desc: It's the Castlehaven Jousting Tournament and all the gang want to win!

programme.title: Peter Rabbit
programme.desc: When Mr Tod tramples on the Shrew's precious dandelions, the angry Shrew vows revenge - but when Cotton-tail follows him into Mr Tod's lair, Peter, Lily and Benjamin must go on a dangerous mission to rescue them both!

programme.title: PJ Masks
programme.desc: Owlette is teaching Owl lot sof stunts and tricks. But Romeo wants some Owl-y power of his own.

programme.title: Bluey

programme.title: Andy And The Band
programme.desc: Leo and Jimi are locked in detention and will miss their gig - can the band bust them out?

programme.title: Kiri and Lou
programme.desc: Kiri and Lou realize that lying is never a good idea.

programme.title: Supertato
programme.desc: The Cobs try to capture Supertato while Evil Pea is on holiday, but it goes wrong resulting in Evil Pea getting covered in flour and custard over in the bath products aisle.

programme.title: Shaun The Sheep

programme.title: Karma's World
programme.desc: Karma hides her guilty pleasure - a secret love for the music of old-timey crooner Romeo Jones.

programme.title: Bluey
programme.desc: (AD) With only five minutes to play 'Driving', Bluey and Mum race against the clock to buy milk for a grumpy guest and have to escape an angry shopkeeper.

programme.title: Spicks And Specks

programme.title: QI
programme.desc: Stephen Fry returns for his final season as host of the quiz show with a difference. Guests include Jimmy Carr, Aisling Bea and Danny Bhoy compete alongside resident panellist Alan Davies.

programme.title: Live At The Apollo
programme.desc: The magnificent Zoe Lyons introduces comedians Ria Lina and Tom Ward to the stage.

programme.title: Whose Line Is It Anyway?
programme.desc: Aisha Tyler hosts another laughter-filled episode of the legendary improv show featuring regulars Wayne Brady, Ryan Stiles and Colin Mochrie along with guest performer Jonathan Mangum.

programme.title: Devolution: A Devo Theory
programme.desc: Enter the minds of one of history's most misunderstood bands. With hits such as 'Whip It' & 'Freedom of Choice', they shared a trailblazing environmental message but were often mocked. 40 years later, we ask: were Devo right?

programme.title: Staged
programme.desc: With the gang reinvigorated, a plan is suggested which could turn failure into glory. But a dangerous question remains: might they need Simon?

programme.title: MythBusters
programme.desc: The A-Team was one of the TV shows that defined the '80s. Adam "Hannibal" Savage and "Howlin' Mad" Hyneman put the cult classic under the MythBusters microscope.

programme.title: Portlandia
programme.desc: Fred and Carrie learn about the art of mixology and love as they venture outside of Portland on a quest. Bryce and Lisa gleefully sing about pickling anything and everything.

programme.title: Portlandia
programme.desc: Doug and Claire become obsessed with a sci-fi television series which becomes an obsession that takes over their lives. Fred and Carrie discuss bad tattoos and their potential to be deal breakers in new relationships.

programme.title: Fleabag
programme.desc: Haunted by memories of her dead best friend, dumped by her boyfriend, and now desperately trying to sell her stolen goods, Fleabag attempts to rekindle romantic fires to distract her from the mayhem of her life.

programme.title: Blunt Talk
programme.desc: As Martin and Rosalie 2 grapple with life-changing news, Walter, Harry, Celia and Jim attend a surrealist ball thrown by the nefarious Rudolphs, hoping to finally obtain a confession.

programme.title: ABC News Update

programme.desc: The toddlers are visited by stuffed animals. Fantus helps a little kangaroo find its parent.
